name: methyl 3-[bis(methylsulfanyl)methyl]-4-cyano-2-hydroxy-2,5-diphenylcyclopent-3-ene-1-carboxylate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-1667
Reason: 3-[Bis(methylsulfanyl)methyl]-4-cyano-2-hydroxy-2,5-diphenylcyclopent-3-ene-1-carboxylate has a complex structure with multiple functional groups that impact its melting point. The basic unit for comparison will be 3-phenyl-2-hydroxy-2,5-diphenylcyclopent-1-one, which has a melting point of -109.4 degrees Celsius. The structural modifications we need to consider are the presence of two additional phenyl rings, a methyl group, a sulfanyl group, and a cyano group. The additional phenyl rings will significantly increase the melting point due to their ability to enhance pi-pi interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each phenyl group may contribute around +30 to +50°C. The methyl group introduces a small increase in molecular weight and rigidity, estimated at around +5°C. The sulfanyl group can participate in hydrogen bonding, which may raise the melting point by approximately +10°C. The cyano group can also contribute to the melting point due to its ability to participate in hydrogen bonding and increase the molecular weight, estimated at around +5°C.
